GRANT – Give permission to user

GRANT SELECT, INSERT
ON schooldb.*
TO 'teacher'@'localhost';
Explanation:teacher user can now:
Read data (SELECT)
Insert data (INSERT)
In all tables of schooldb.

REVOKE INSERT
ON schooldb.*
FROM 'teacher'@'localhost';
Explanation:teacher can no longer insert data, but can still SELECT.

25)HANDSON-7: SQL Operators and Conditions

1. AS (Alias)
Alias gives temporary name to column.
SELECT studentname,
       studentage,
       studentage + 5 AS agein5yrs
FROM students
WHERE studentage < 25;
studentname   studentage  agein5yrs

2. AND (Multiple conditions)
SELECT studentname, studentcity, studentage
FROM students
WHERE studentcity = 'Delhi'
AND studentage > 22;
studentname  studentcity  studentage

3. NOT (Exclude condition)
studentname
studentage

4. Even studentscore
Even number → remainder = 0
SELECT studentname, studentscore
FROM students
WHERE studentscore % 2 = 0;
studentname studentscore

5. BETWEEN (Range)
SELECT studentname, studentage
FROM students
WHERE studentage BETWEEN 20 AND 24;
studentname  studentage

6. IN (Multiple values match)
studentname    studentcity

7. NOT IN (Exclude values)
SELECT studentname, studentcity
FROM students
WHERE studentcity NOT IN ('Delhi', 'Pune');
studentname  studentcity
